<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,442,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
In the text of (
<bibRefCitation author="Artuz, M. L. &amp; Fricke, R." box="[350,575,478,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" pagination="545 - 565" refId="ref3676" refString="Artuz, M. L. &amp; Fricke, R. (2019) The marine teleost fishes of the Sea of Marmara; an updated and annotated checklist. Zootaxa, 4565 (4), 545 - 565. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4565.4.9" type="journal article" year="2019">Artüz &amp; Fricke 2019</bibRefCitation>
P: 547) the subject is explained with the following paragraph, which is repeated below to avoid any misunderstanding;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,442,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
“ 
<bibRefCitation author="Deveciyan, K." box="[205,405,550,574]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref4118" refString="Deveciyan, K. (1915) Balik ve balikcilik. Duyun-i Osmaniye varidat-i mahsuse idare-yi merkeziyesi matbaasi, Istanbul, 60 pp. [in Ottomane]" type="book" year="1915">Deveciyan (1915)</bibRefCitation>
noticed that the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName authority="limanda" authorityName="limanda (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[811,1001,550,574]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Limanda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="limanda">Limanda limanda</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1051,1287,550,574]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Pleuronectes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="limanda">Pleuronectes limanda</taxonomicName>
) included the Black Sea and Sea of Marmara. Since this record cannot be currently confirmed, it is possible that it was based on misidentified Platichthys 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[469,533,622,646]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Pleuronectes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flesus">flesus</taxonomicName>
, although he also reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[824,911,622,646]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Pleuronectes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flesus">P. flesus</taxonomicName>
(as Pleuronectes flessus) in the same publication as a separate species. Therefore, we include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[675,790,658,682]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pleuronectidae" genus="Pleuronectes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="limanda">L. limanda</taxonomicName>
in the checklist with some reservation.”
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
